============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/17-9e42f14/improvement-plan.md`. Here's the summary:

**Three concentric fixes for the `WARZYWA` failure:**

1. **Expand `SECTION_LABELS`** — Add ~25 Polish food-category chapter headers (warzywa, mieso, ryby, zupy, desery, etc.). This alone fixes the current failure by filtering `WARZYWA` before it ever enters scoring.

2. **Position-aware single-ALL_CAPS guard** — When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives and it sits in the last 25% of the document, prefer the best earlier candidate. Catches future category footers not in the set.

3. **Reduce `allCapsBonus` for single-word candidates** — Drop from +0.08 to +0.03 for single-word ALL_CAPS. Multi-word ALL_CAPS keep full bonus. This narrows the score gap so the position factor on line-0 candidates becomes decisive.

These form defense-in-depth layers: Change 1 catches known labels at the hard-filter stage, Change 3 weakens unknown single-word labels at scoring, and Change 2 provides a structural last resort at the guard stage. No regressions expected on the other 10 passing recipes.
