{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WXJ8YPSzkXSDBPsZPnb8VX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the key information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the iterations history.\n\n## Summary of Title Extraction Iterations 14-17\n\nBased on my thorough read of all the documentation, here's the complete history:\n\n### **Iteration 14** (81.8% accuracy — 9/11 passing)\n\n**Commit:** `dfda596 - docs: explain title extraction`\n\nTwo failures introduced after corpus expansion:\n\n1. **LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS** → Got `WITH NIGELLA + SEEDS`\n   - Root cause: 4-line title never fits in candidate pool (max 3-line joins). The 3-line join `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA` is destroyed by dedup because `WITH NIGELLA` (single line) is a substring.\n\n2. **Smażona zielona fasolka** → Got `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM`\n   - Root cause: ALL_CAPS translation line receives +0.10 structural bonus, beating the mixed-case Polish title which gets no bonus. Bilingual detection threshold (0.4 cosine similarity) too strict for Polish-Korean pairs with completely different word roots.\n\n**Planned fixes:** Short ALL_CAPS line merge pass (for 4+ line titles) + layout-based bilingual detection (instead of embedding similarity).\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 15** (72.7% accuracy — 8/11 passing)\n\n**Commit:** `b8dddbe - title-extraction: iteration 15`\n\nThree new failures introduced by the iteration 14 fixes:\n\n1. **KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA** → Got `UuIw`\n   - Root cause A: Breadcrumb line `/ Jesien / Zupy` (with forward slashes) triggers false bilingual detection, suppressing the real ALL_CAPS title.\n   - Root cause B: `UuIw` escapes garbled-text filter (4 letters, vowel ratio 0.75, no mid-word casing transition check).\n\n2. **LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS** → Got `BALLS`\n   - Root cause: Metadata line `MAKES 25 LABANEH BALLS` fragments. The metadata filter catches the prefix, but `BALLS` orphaned on next line. It then destroys the correctly-merged title via \"shorter wins\" dedup.\n\n3. **Smażona zielona fasolka** → Got `DLA & OSOB`\n   - Root cause: OCR corruption `4 → &` in `DLA 4 OSÓB` defeats the digit-dependent metadata filter. The corrupted metadata receives ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) and beats the mixed-case title.\n\n**Planned fixes:** \n- Breadcrumb filter (2+ slashes)\n- Mid-word casing transition detection for garbled text\n- Metadata continuation suppression (skip short ALL_CAPS after metadata)\n- OCR-resilient DLA pattern matching\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 16** (90.9% accuracy — 10/11 passing)\n\n**Commit:** `e59482e - title-extraction: iteration 16`\n\nOnly one failure remains:\n\n**Smażona zielona fasolka** → Got `''` (empty/undefined)\n\nRoot causes (three):\n1. **Bilingual join contamination:** Multi-line joins like `\"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` embed the translation but start with the primary title, so they pass the bilingual filter (which only checks `startsWith`). The English vocabulary boosts their embedding score above the clean Polish-only candidate.\n\n2. **Structural bonus misallocation:** `isStructuralHeading(\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\")` fires correctly, assigning the +0.10 bonus to the translation before bilingual detection runs. This inflates the threshold, pushing the Polish title below the cutoff.\n\n3. **Diacritic-stripped section labels:** OCR returns `SKLADNIKI` (without ą), but `SECTION_LABELS` stores `\"składniki\"` (with ą). The normalization doesn't strip diacritics, so the check fails.\n\n**Planned fixes:**\n- Extend bilingual suppression to catch embedded translations (endsWith, includes with space prefix)\n- Reassign structural bonus when heading is identified as translation (post-hoc recomputation)\n- Diacritic-insensitive section label matching (NFKD normalization)\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 17** (90.9% accuracy — 10/11 passing)\n\n**Commit:** `9e42f14 - title-extraction: iteration 17`\n\nIteration 16 fixes completed, but a **different failure** now appears:\n\n**Faszerowana papryka** → Got `WARZYWA`\n\nRoot causes:\n1. **Polish chapter/category labels missing from SECTION_LABELS:** `WARZYWA` (vegetables) is a recipe-book category footer, not a recipe title. It's not in the section labels set, so it passes all hard filters.\n\n2. **Multi-title guard positionally blind:** When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives (here: `WARZYWA`), the guard unconditionally collapses to the highest scorer. This works for real ALL_CAPS titles but fails when an ALL_CAPS section label happens to score higher due to the +0.08 bonus, especially if it appears late in the document.\n\n3. **ALL_CAPS bonus unconditional:** Single-word ALL_CAPS terms like `WARZYWA` receive +0.08 even though they're not structural headings. This amplifies weak category-label candidates.\n\n**Trajectory:** The fixes each iteration address one set of failures but expose pre-existing gaps in how the algorithm handles multilingual layouts, OCR corruption, and category/section labels.\n\n---\n\n### **Current State**\n\n- **10 of 11 recipes passing** (90.9% accuracy)\n- **1 failure:** Faszerowana papryka → extracting section label instead of title\n- **iter.txt tracking:** Shows accuracy per recipe across all 17 iterations; latest run shows recipe 5 (Faszerowana papryka) failing\n\nThe architecture is fundamentally sound — all improvements have been surgical fixes to the filter layer rather than redesigns of the pipeline itself."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af0ef68d210537552 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 93043\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 54236</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e646be9-92d4-4481-9255-b1f94813f9c6","uuid":"3fccde16-7658-49ba-8e95-752e8cf8d67a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read all files in tools/title-loop/docs/ to understand what has been tried in previous iterations. I need:\n1. The iter.txt file\n2. Any feedback