{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JEC8cGz44tKoLiSTaXFoLE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me outline my proposed changes and then write the improvement plan.\n\n**Key proposals for the `WARZYWA` failure:**\n\n1. **Expand `SECTION_LABELS` with Polish food-category labels** — \"warzywa\", \"mieso\", \"ryby\", \"desery\", \"zupy\", etc. are recipe-book chapter headers, not titles. This is the most direct fix.\n\n2. **Position-aware multi-title guard** — When exactly 1 ALL_CAPS candidate survives and it appears in the last ~25% of the document (after body content), prefer the earlier mixed-case candidate instead of blindly collapsing to highest score.\n\n3. **Attenuate `allCapsBonus` for single-word ALL_CAPS** — Single-word ALL_CAPS terms are far more likely to be category labels than recipe titles. Reduce or eliminate the +0.08 bonus for single-word candidates.\n\nLet me check what's already in the target directory and write the plan."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1745,"cache_read_input_tokens":35225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1745},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e646be9-92d4-4481-9255-b1f94813f9c6","uuid":"a444ae9a-eca0-4c12-ba07-ed207061a0ad"}
